suncertify.client
Interface RoomReservationsModel

All Superinterfaces:
TableModel
All Known Implementing Classes:
URLyBirdModel
public interface RoomReservationsModel
extends TableModel

A model for the list of hotel rooms returned by a search. Model is a two-dimensional representation of the data, consisting of rows and columns.

Interface is part of a Model-View-Controller architecture for the hotel room reservation system. By extending the TableModel interface, the design reuses the Observer design pattern inherent in this interface and the "observers" that implement the TableModelListener interface. Implementations of this interface are then the "observables" in the Observer pattern.

When the model updates its data, it will notify the view as an observer of the model to refresh itself with the latest data via implementations of the TableModel and TableModelListener interfaces.

Author:
Oliver Hernandez
See Also:
TableModel, TableModelListener

findRooms

void findRooms(String hotelName,
               String city)
               throws RemoteException
Find all the hotel rooms that match the search criteria passed in. The search criteria is case-sensitive. A match occurs when the room field exactly matches or begins with the search criteria. For example, a hotel named "Sunny Inn" will match "Sun" and "Sunny", in addition to "Sunny Inn".

Parameters:
hotelName - the hotel name to search rooms by.
city - the city to search rooms by.
Throws:
RemoteException - when a network error occurs.

bookRoom

boolean bookRoom(int rowId,
                 String customerId)
                 throws RemoteException,
                        RecordNotFoundException,
                        SecurityException
Book the hotel room at the specified row in the model.

Parameters:
rowId - a zero-based row index.
customerId - the customer ID to book the room for.
Returns:
true when the room was successfully booked for the customer, false otherwise.
Throws:
RemoteException - when a network error occurs.
RecordNotFoundException - when the room has been deleted.
SecurityException - when the room was attempted to be booked by another user, or the request to book the room timed-out.

isRoomBooked

Returns whether or not the model displayed to the view has the selected room booked. The view would show a value in the Customer ID column if the room was booked.

Parameters:
selectedRoom - the row index of the room selected by the view.
Returns:
true if the selected room is booked, false otherwise.
